			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I could easily be wrong here, but I thought that the "pets don't get agro if a PC is in range" change happened because some enchanters were using charmed pets (this is pre-luclin, before Dire Charm) to tank Vindi in Kael.  So enchanters were the cause of this change, and not us.
<br />

<br />
And Sepikai is right.  Dire Charm makes enchanters (and druids in many cases) have WAY better pet damage than we do, with no corresponding risk of charm breaking.  Wasn't that the original idea when ANY type of charm went in?  That by charming and having a POWERFUL pet, that your ran the risk of it turning on you?  Now that risk is gone.
<br />

<br />
I don't begrudge Dire Charm.  I think the enchanters and others should have it.  No problem.  But don't make us useless along the way!  Our pet output plus nukes can't compare to a Dire-charmed pet, while the enchanter STILL has the excellent utility of slow/mez.
<br />

<br />
And despite what you say Churizo, beastlords still have awesome DPS w/o a pet.  And then the pet is added in.  And then they have their utility with slow and bst crack.  I've been in quite a few teir2/3 PoP groups where the 65 Bst is the slower.  And most of bst DPS does NOT USE MANA!  Mages do.
<br />

<br />
Mages need something to bring our DPS in line.  And I think the comparison with existing DPS and former DPS by % added damage done by samxp is great one.  It tells DPS now, and how much increased it will be by these changes in the future.
<br />

<br />
As for pets tanking for PCs, I think this would be OK if they took out the ability for charmed pets to do it.  They were the problem, not the "normal" pets.
<br />

<br />
Eriol</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
